race.comment: STRAIGHT SETS (11) has not been produced since leading for home before dropping out on debut over 1250m at Canterbury in June. Well backed that day so more was expected. Three recent trials should have her ready to return in a positive manner. UNCLE BARRY (2) added to a frustrating tally of minor placings when a closing second over this course and distance 16 days ago. Worth another chance with winkers going on for the first time. INVINCIBLE PHANTOM (8) is a flyer who has led for the judge but folded late in two runs this prep, both over 1100m at Goulburn. Coming back to 900m makes a lot of sense. Will give backers a great sight. OAKFIELD MARS (6) returns for a second campaign off a six-month break. Best of two runs last prep was a second on debut here at this distance. Recent trial winner who is ready to run a big race. COOL BLAZE (3) didn't impress first-up at Goulburn but can improve coming back in journey.
